1
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,133
<i>- Dad! Dad!
- Victor!</i>

2
00:00:12,267 --> 00:00:14,067
<i> Are you behind all of this?</i>

3
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:15,167
<i> Let go of me!</i>

4
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:16,400
<i>Aren't there a lot of people
angry at you?</i>

5
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:17,600
<i> Why are you blaming me?</i>

6
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:18,900
<i> It's over, Joaquin.</i>

7
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:22,667
<i>Your public image
is completely ruined.</i>

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,533
<i>This is bigger
than your rivalry with Victor.</i>

9
00:00:25,667 --> 00:00:27,767
<i>People will lose
their trust in you.</i>

10
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,700
<i>This is Mayor Joaquin Guerrero,
Mira.</i>

11
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,467
<i>Are you ready
for your big break?</i>

12
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,533
<i> Ms. Beautiful!</i>

13
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:33,533
<i>You really don't want
to leave this place?</i>

14
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,267
<i> I just noticed in the video...</i>

15
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:37,033
<i> it sounded like a name Batsi.</i>

16
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,933
<i>Sebastian Placido, alias Batsi.</i>

17
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:40,367
<i>Sir, we might get in trouble...</i>

18
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,567
<i>If you don't want to come,
then don't.</i>

19
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:47,100
<i>I admit I didn't react well to
my daughter's abduction.</i>

20
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:49,900
<i>Victor Santiago, I'm asking
for your forgiveness.</i>

21
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:53,267
<i> El Hepe, 50 million.</i>

22
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,300
<i>I'll text the address and time.</i>

23
00:00:55,433 --> 00:00:57,500
<i>I want that animal
captured alive...</i>

24
00:00:57,633 --> 00:01:00,067
<i>I need to know
who's behind this.</i>

25
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:02,500
<i>Sir, they said they're already
at the exchange site with Mayor.</i>

26
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:04,233
<i>- No movement yet.
- Boss Tonyo.</i>

27
00:01:04,367 --> 00:01:05,667
<i>We just want
to ask you something.</i>

28
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:08,800
<i>Sorry about the mess, Boss,
the house is a little chaotic.</i>

29
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,367
<i> El Hepe!</i>

30
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:12,533
<i> This belongs to Faye.</i>

31
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:13,500
I don't know that person, Boss.

32
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:14,867
Lieutenant Conde!

33
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,667
What is it, Enriquez?

34
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:41,400
Let's go!

35
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:50,633
The kidnappers are here.

36
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:57,067
Mayor!

37
00:02:57,733 --> 00:02:59,200
You all did well.

38
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:01,667
Oh, there's Faye!

39
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,000
- There's Faye!
- Mom, Mom.

40
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:09,400
You monsters.

41
00:03:09,533 --> 00:03:12,967
Faye, sweetheart,
daddy's here now.

42
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,033
We can go home.

43
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,033
She can't hear you now, Mayor.

44
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:21,900
She's in a deep sleep now.

45
00:03:22,067 --> 00:03:24,200
What now? Are we going down?

46
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:25,667
Mom, wait.

47
00:03:26,233 --> 00:03:27,200
Let them be.

48
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:30,167
Oh my God, there she is.

49
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:31,500
The money is there.

50
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:32,500
Give me back my daughter!

51
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:33,733
Give me that!

52
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:37,367
No one moves until
the exchange is complete.

53
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,467
We need to make sure
that the victim is safe.

54
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,000
Copy, Chief.

55
00:03:45,533 --> 00:03:47,833
There. Hey, check it out!

56
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:50,567
Once the Mayor
secures the package,

57
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:51,933
we move in.

58
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:53,800
What's the status
on the roadblocks?

59
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:55,667
<i> They've got no way out, Chief.</i>

60
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,667
Check it if it's real.

61
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,167
What? Is it real?

62
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,533
Boss, it's real.

63
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:04,600
Give me back my daughter.

64
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:09,967
Mayor, are you sure you didn't
bring any cops with you?

65
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:14,000
No.

66
00:04:14,133 --> 00:04:15,800
I'm sure.

67
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:17,367
All right, Mayor.

68
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,267
But before you join her,

69
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:22,700
I want you to turn around

70
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:24,633
and raise your hands.

71
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:27,667
Don't want to, Mayor?

72
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,733
Turn around!

73
00:04:29,867 --> 00:04:30,733
Oh.

74
00:04:30,867 --> 00:04:32,433
Oh, oh, oh, oh.

75
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:33,633
Hands up...

76
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:35,267
Hands up!

77
00:04:37,533 --> 00:04:38,700
Dance, Mayor.

78
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:40,800
Dance, Mayor, dance.

79
00:04:40,933 --> 00:04:43,500
There, there, dance, Mayor.

80
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:45,967
Don't you dare turn around,
Mayor!

81
00:04:46,867 --> 00:04:49,567
All units,
move towards to target!

82
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,700
Secure the victim!

83
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:51,700
Move, move, move!

84
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:53,033
Move, move, move!

85
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,467
Let's move, let's move!

86
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,467
Hurry!

87
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,500
Come on, hurry up!

88
00:05:09,933 --> 00:05:11,633
- Let's go, come on.
- Move!

89
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:14,100
Daddy's here now.

90
00:05:14,867 --> 00:05:16,533
Dear...

91
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:26,733
Mayor!

92
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:27,833
- Faye!
- Dear!

93
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:29,100
- Mom!
- Dear!

94
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,833
- Faye!
- Dear!

95
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,300
What is this? What is this?

96
00:05:35,467 --> 00:05:38,033
- Dad...
- Where's Faye?

97
00:05:38,167 --> 00:05:39,733
- Joaquin!
- Dad, what happened?

98
00:05:39,867 --> 00:05:40,867
We've been played.

99
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:46,200
Major, bring those
bastards to me

100
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,800
as soon as possible!

101
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:49,000
Yes, Mayor.

102
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,267
It's Ms. Faye.

103
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,467
You're safe now.

104
00:07:07,367 --> 00:07:09,267
Something feels off.

105
00:07:18,767 --> 00:07:20,233
Get our gear.

106
00:07:20,367 --> 00:07:21,933
Yes, Boss.

107
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:26,233
Would you look at our luck.

108
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:28,367
Turns out,
Batsi was the only answer.

109
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,600
Let's go, we can't stay here
any longer.

110
00:07:31,733 --> 00:07:33,200
Come on!

111
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:36,200
We'll take you back to your
family now, Ms. Faye.

112
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:38,200
Miss, thank you so much.

113
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:06,800
Let's go.

114
00:08:22,133 --> 00:08:24,833
Die, all of you!

115
00:08:25,633 --> 00:08:26,833
This way! Go, go!

116
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:28,133
Hurry, hurry!

117
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:32,333
Take cover, take cover!

118
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:34,133
Sir, what do we do?

119
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:36,800
Surround them!

120
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,467
Let's find
a way around the back!

121
00:08:45,867 --> 00:08:47,367
Let's go!

122
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,033
Come on! Here.

123
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:16,433
Stay there, don't move!

124
00:09:55,467 --> 00:09:57,267
Noble! Dizon!

125
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,533
Get back in the car.
We'll handle it from here!

126
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:02,367
Go ahead.

127
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:04,667
- Enriquez, let's go!
- Okay, okay!

128
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:07,000
Stay here.

129
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:08,933
I'll go help Lieutenant Conde.

130
00:11:24,867 --> 00:11:26,233
Bro.

131
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,000
Thank you.

132
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,233
Drink first.

133
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:45,000
Conde!

134
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:53,533
You two,
you're really hard-headed.

135
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:59,233
Good job.

136
00:12:03,033 --> 00:12:04,033
Thank you, Sir.

137
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:08,433
Next time you disobey my orders,

138
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:10,367
you both better watch
yourselves...

139
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,933
especially you!

140
00:12:12,767 --> 00:12:14,367
- Copy, Major.
- Faye!

141
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,333
- Where is my daughter?
- Faye!

142
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,733
- Faye!
- Faye!

143
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:18,833
Daddy?

144
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:19,967
- My daughter!
- Faye!

145
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:22,100
- Daddy...
- My dear...

146
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:45,667
It doesn't matter anymore,
Joaquin.

147
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,500
The damage has been done.

148
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:07,467
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

149
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,067
Faye...

150
00:13:10,533 --> 00:13:11,833
Daddy...

151
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:13,467
Are you okay?

152
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:16,200
- It's done, it's done.
- You are safe. You are safe.

153
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:20,033
Secure the hospital.

154
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:22,500
Keep that one alive.

155
00:13:23,133 --> 00:13:25,700
Whoever's behind this will pay.

156
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:27,300
Yes, Mayor.

157
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:33,300
Lieutenant Conde...

158
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:34,967
we meet again.

159
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:40,200
My office is always
open for you.

160
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:44,500
And for you too,
Sergeant Enriquez.

161
00:13:44,633 --> 00:13:46,133
Just tell me what you need.

162
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:47,900
Thank you, Mayor.

163
00:13:48,967 --> 00:13:52,267
Major, assign Conde

164
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:56,133
to the investigation team for
the San Isidro bank robbery.

165
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:03,100
I need a top-notch cop
on that case.

166
00:14:12,667 --> 00:14:16,067
Thank you very much,
Lieutenant Conde.

167
00:14:18,867 --> 00:14:20,700
Thank you, Mayor.

168
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:24,533
You too...

169
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:26,200
Mayor.

170
00:14:37,967 --> 00:14:41,333
Thanks to all of you.

171
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,433
Come on, let's go.

172
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:48,600
Oh, Dad...

173
00:14:49,533 --> 00:14:50,400
Wait.

174
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:53,200
All right.

175
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:17,033
Thank you so much,
Sergeant Enriquez.

176
00:15:20,133 --> 00:15:22,833
Can I call you sister?

177
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:25,167
Of course.

178
00:15:49,967 --> 00:15:51,900
Take care, okay?

179
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:54,667
Thank you, Sister.

180
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:41,700
Welcome to the dream team.
There you go.

181
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:44,133
You know, I'm really excited
to work with you here.

182
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:45,800
Have a seat, go on.

183
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:51,167
You should've brought...

184
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,933
Enriquez with you,
so we'd have a muse around.

185
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,833
Oh, by the way...

186
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:00,567
Just want to make it
clear to you...

187
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:06,000
that Robles and I are still
the leads on this case.

188
00:17:06,133 --> 00:17:08,467
Just in case,
you know what I mean.

189
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:10,200
Don't worry, Bok.

190
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:12,933
The credit's all yours.
I'm just here to do my job.

191
00:17:13,067 --> 00:17:14,700
It's better to make thing clear.

192
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:17,400
Oh...

193
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:18,967
by the way...

194
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:23,267
Do you think the kidnapper
will actually talk?

195
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:25,700
- Why do you ask?
- Oh...

196
00:17:26,267 --> 00:17:27,733
Well, I just feel like
he's saying that

197
00:17:27,867 --> 00:17:30,333
so he can stay alive.

198
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:34,633
But, but I also think

199
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:41,133
his buddies are planning to
break him out of the hospital.

200
00:17:41,267 --> 00:17:43,233
That's what happens in TV
dramas, right?

201
00:17:44,100 --> 00:17:45,600
It's possible, isn't it?

202
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:47,033
Oh.

203
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,900
Conde.

204
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:51,633
Has Enriquez arrived yet?

205
00:17:51,767 --> 00:17:53,333
Not yet, Sir.

206
00:17:53,467 --> 00:17:56,600
Tell her to head straight
to the hospital.

207
00:17:56,733 --> 00:17:58,567
The Mayor's expecting us.

208
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:00,833
Yes, Sir.

209
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,700
Enriquez!

210
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:19,933
Sir.

211
00:18:23,167 --> 00:18:25,833
I haven't gotten the chance
to thank you yet.

212
00:18:25,967 --> 00:18:27,033
For what, Sir?

213
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,533
Because I got into the team

214
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:31,800
investigating
the San Isidro bank robbery...

215
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:34,700
because of you.

216
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,800
Thank you so much.

217
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:39,100
It's nothing, Lieutenant Conde.

218
00:18:39,933 --> 00:18:41,833
Just call me Tonyo.

219
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,333
Thank you, thank you.

220
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,800
Good morning!

221
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:16,500
Morning.

222
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:19,233
Joaquin, look at this.

223
00:19:19,367 --> 00:19:22,167
Doesn't Sergeant Bobby Enriquez
look like someone?

224
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:24,100
Really? Who?

225
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:26,567
Your mistress, Amanda.

226
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,233
Don't they look alike?

227
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,100
Wait.

228
00:19:30,533 --> 00:19:32,433
What exactly are you
getting at here?

229
00:19:33,167 --> 00:19:34,867
You do know the family
just went through

230
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,567
a traumatic experience, right?

231
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:39,200
And now you're telling me this?

232
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:41,833
What is your problem?

233
00:19:42,233 --> 00:19:43,833
Sorry, okay? Sorry.

234
00:19:43,967 --> 00:19:46,367
It's just, for me...

235
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:49,600
If anyone related to you is
going to get hurt

236
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:50,967
because of this politics mess,

237
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:55,367
maybe it should be the child
you had out of wedlock...

238
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:58,200
wherever she is.

239
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,800
Sir, did you hear?

240
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:17,000
They're transferring the
kidnapper to a regular room.

241
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:19,500
We'll be able to talk
to him soon.

242
00:20:21,067 --> 00:20:23,900
You got a theory on
what he's gonna spill?

243
00:20:24,467 --> 00:20:26,433
Usually you have, right?

244
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:28,733
But this time, Sir, nothing.

245
00:20:30,933 --> 00:20:32,467
<i> Paging Doctor Gutierrez,</i>

246
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:35,433
<i>please proceed
to the operating room.</i>

247
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,067
Oh, forensics just messaged me

248
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:40,533
ballistics results are in.

249
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,767
What did they say?

250
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,533
They found a match
for the bullet.

251
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:57,600
He was part of
the San Isidro bank robbery.

252
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:16,967
I guess this is the part
where you going to tell me...

253
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:20,600
what your favor's going to cost
me.

254
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:23,000
Dizon, Noble,
man the main entrance.

255
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:24,000
Get the names of everyone

256
00:21:24,133 --> 00:21:25,833
who's gone in or out
of this hospital

257
00:21:25,967 --> 00:21:27,200
in the last 24 hours.

258
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:29,867
Garcia, check all CCTV footage

259
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,267
for the last 24 hours.

260
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,300
Conde, Enriquez,

261
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:34,267
interview the entire
hospital staff.

262
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:37,033
I want to know who had access
to our kidnapper.

263
00:21:37,167 --> 00:21:38,467
Here is what will do, Nurse Pam.

264
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:42,600
Let's say someone wanted to
switch the medicine

265
00:21:42,767 --> 00:21:44,367
meant for a patient.

266
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:47,800
Where and when would they most
likely be able to do that?

267
00:21:47,933 --> 00:21:49,767
Well, sometimes...

268
